        <detaileddescription>
<para>Create a &quot;value&quot; (slider/drag/...). <computeroutput>T</computeroutput> must be a scalar; vector support must be implemented manually. Pass <computeroutput>min &gt;= max</computeroutput> to disable the range checks. If this returns true, use the new value in place of the current one. <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>consumeValueOverride</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If true - retrieves (deletes) a value from storage. If false - copies the value from the storage (saves the original to the storage to be retrieved again, for example, in the next frame) </para>
